          "name": "ce32",
          "text": "A conversation between David Sloan Wilson and Daniel Wahl",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "H4"
        },
        {
          "id": "3c340f4874f4_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "20bb",
          "text": "On July 22nd I had the privilege of being able to interview and learn from one of the most respected evolutionary theorist of the Century. It was such a pleasure to meet David Sloan Wilson and it motivated me to take a deep dive into his work before hopefully deepening my collaboration with him in the future.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "3c340f4874f4_4",
          "href": null,
          "name": "0009",
          "text": "Here is what we talked about in key words and a short summary (I hope to make a full transcript available after my summer break):",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "3c340f4874f4_5",
          "href": null,
          "name": "f02b",
          "text": "— an appreciation of complexity",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "3c340f4874f4_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "7e53",
          "text": "— the history of the study of evolution from Darwin, via the genetic reductionism of the 20th Century, to the insight that evolution offers a grand synthesis of human related knowledge when “Darwinian Evolution is understood as any process that combines the three ingredients of variation, selection and replication.”",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "3c340f4874f4_7",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b193",
          "text": "— David distinguishes between non-living and living complex systems and we explore to what degree complex systems are always unpredictable and uncontrollable",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "3c340f4874f4_8",
          "href": null,
          "name": "e554",
          "text": "— we explore David’s and E.O. Wilson’s famous sentence “Selfishness beats altruism within groups. Altruistic groups beat selfish groups. All else is commentary.”",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "3c340f4874f4_9",
          "href": null,
          "name": "60ee",
          "text": "— the evolutionary imperative of redesigning the human impact on Earth and the importance of a bioregional focus in this endeavour",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "3c340f4874f4_10",
          "href": null,
          "name": "e50a",
          "text": "— David shares some of his learnings from working with Elenor Ostrom when she was defining the 8 principles of managing the commons successfully",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "3c340f4874f4_11",
          "href": null,
          "name": "816d",
          "text": "— We discuss the enabling preconditions for successful commons management",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "3c340f4874f4_12",
          "href": null,
          "name": "9645",
          "text": "— David speaks about the Prosocial.world project that he has helped to create",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "3c340f4874f4_13",
          "href": null,
          "name": "8e1e",
          "text": "— We explore how many different movements and sub-cultures have evolved procedures and methodologies that are aligned with the theory behind pro-social",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "3c340f4874f4_14",
          "href": null,
          "name": "edba",
          "text": "— (1:06) We speak about the concept of ‘subsidiarity’ and its history (Catholic origins and a founding principle of the European Union) — Applying a pro-social approach at the bioregional scale and implementing Ostrom’s principles (& whether it would need a redesign or replacement of the current economic system)",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "3c340f4874f4_15",
          "href": null,
          "name": "e2f4",
          "text": "— (1:13) DSW on social market economies like the Nordic countries",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "3c340f4874f4_16",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b9d8",
          "text": "— (1:17) critique of the orthodoxy of economic theory and the need for a paradigmatic change — letting go of ‘homo economicus’ … DSW mentions ‘doughnut economics’ as the “third way” that adopts a more systemic approach to thinking about economics",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "3c340f4874f4_17",
          "href": null,
          "name": "a72c",
          "text": "— (1:22) we explore how DSW and his team could support a bioregional approach on the Balearic Islands, including also collaboration with the Doughnut Economics Action Lab, the Capital Institute, and Commonland Foundation …",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "3c340f4874f4_18",
          "href": null,
          "name": "f929",
          "text": "— (1:28) DSW shares about his meeting Dennis Snower (of the Kiel Institute for the World Economy) and getting a grant to help others implement ‘pro-social’ (offering a workshop to organisations including DEAL, C40, EMF, Transition Network, …) and highlights the potential synergies of bringing these networks together around place, city or region focussed efforts …",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "3c340f4874f4_19",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4bc3",
          "text": "— (1:39) DSW offering some possible way of getting involved with a project here on Mallorca once I have managed to get a committed core group together to land such a collaboration …",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "3c340f4874f4_20",
          "href": null,
          "name": "bdca",
          "text": "A link to a full transcript will be added here (in a month or so when I have it)!",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
